Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
print_message(25.10)                                      print_message(25.10)

Name
       print_message - Generates a message that is included in the report_mes-
       sage output if the message is designated as an error or a warning

Syntax
       print_message

       -help

       [-id <msgID> | <formatString>]

       [<args>]

       [-error]

       [-warning]

       Generates  a  message  that is included in the report_message output if
       the message is designated as an error or a warning.

Parameters
       <args> Specifies the format argument value to print.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -error Specifies the message is an error. A prefix will be added.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       <formatString>
              Specify the format specifier like sprintf or Tcl's  format  com-
              mand.

              Data_type: string, required

       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each print_message parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man print_message.

       -id <msgID>
              Specifies the message id.

       -warning
              Specifies that the message is a warning. A prefix will be added.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       Examples
       The following commands generate an error and a message, which  are  in-
       cluded in the report_message output:

       [DEV]innovus> print_message -error "A test %s." "from the user"

       ERROR: (user): A test from the user.

       innovus> print_message -warning "A test %s." "from the user"

       WARN: (user): A test from the user.

       innovus> print_message "A test %s." "from the user"

       A test from the user.

       innovus > report_message

       *** Summary of all messages that are not suppressed in this session:

       Severity      ID       Count         Summary

       ERROR       no_id       1            A test %s.

       ERROR       user        1            A test %s.

       WARN        user        1            A test %s.

       *** Message Summary: 1 warning(s), 2 error(s)

Related Information
